rComments: Took CSC263 with him in the Summer 2016 term. He is very good at explaining even the toughest concepts and makes you feel excited about the material. Throughout the term it was very obvious that he cares a lot about his students. Would definitely take a course with him again.
Great prof, very clear and to-the-point lectures. Always helpful and pretty friendly during office hours. Also, I'm just writing this since I saw he had a 3.0 rating, which I think is WAY TOO LOW!

He is a very nice person first of all. It is true that he doesn't post any slides nor notes because he is expecting and encouraging you to come to class and participate in the lectures and tutorials. For those who didn't like him, probably cuz you didn't go to class or lecture. It is on you. I worked hard and it paid off. The material is hard!
